s or takes a short position in the full range of financial instruments including  investment grade corporate debt high yield bonds leveraged loans and distressed debt  structured credit products which may include commercial and residential mortgage securities aircraft securitization and other assetbacked structured securities  trade claims  value oriented equities in companies and industries experiencing stress or dislocation and  credit default swaps although they do not use direct leverage their clients may be exposed to indirect leverage when gcm on a limited basis utilizes equity and bond short sales credit and currency derivative products and various index products to hedge and or enhance their trading strategies in the news see more euroweek january   equity capital markets news in brief january   euroweek january   equity capital markets news in brief january   see full news coverage and complete stories with relsci professional create your news feed see more executives  employees matthew s barrett founding partner david john poulten chief operating officer michael montgomery chief compliance officer eitan jacob simon melamed limited partner managing director holly kim limited partner managing director brian d berman limited partner managing director chris sayer vice president  portfolio manager paths to glendon capital management lp glendon capital management lp you connections via relationship science glendon capital management lp sync your contacts to see how you can connect with glendon capital management lp start my free trial ‚û§ see more advisors  consultants companies ‚ñæ prime broker deutsche bank ag deutsche bank ag engages in the provision of corporate banking and investment services it operates through the following segments global markets gm corporate and investment banking cib private wealth and commercial clients pwcc deutsche asset management deutsche am postbank pb and noncore operations unit ncou the gm segment includes the sales and trading related activities of the former corporate banking and securities segment the cib segment comprises of the combined corporate business components of the corporate banking and securities and global transaction banking businesses the pwcc segment covers german and international private and commercial clients businesses the deutsche am segment contains the asset management activities the pb segment reflects the core components and noncore components of postbank the ncou segment no longer contains the aforementioned noncore components related to postbank the company was founded by adelbert delbrueck on march   and is headquartered in frankfurt am main germany clients companies ‚ñæ ohio police  fire pension fund ¬†‚Ä¢ ¬†columbus oh the ohio police  fire pension fund employs an asset allocation strategy in which a risk parity approach adopted allows a portion of the portfolio to be conservatively leveraged their objective is to reduce the total expected risk of the portfolio without sacrificing the expected return this approach balances the funds exposure among investment classes that perform differently in various economic and market environments the ohio police  fire pension invests in us equities nonus equities fixedincome global inflation protected securities high yield bonds real estate private markets and cash holdings  top positions restricted data only for relsci professional users start my free trial ‚û§ see more youve reached your  free profiles limit this month upgrade to relsci pro today to enjoy unlimited article views and much more start my free trial ‚û§ still not convinced check out our full listing of features here are you a relsci pro subscriber login to relsci pro¬† ‚û§ not a pro subscriber log in here to manage your alerts keep me signed in login¬† ‚û§ forgot your password i have read the lexisnexis terms  conditions sign me up¬† ‚û§ microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browser your browser history must allow fi